Sandwich - Class in cscd211Classes
This class represents a Sandwich.
A Sandwich is comprised of a String for the Sandwich name, an int for the calories contained in the sandwich and a String array of the toppings on the sandwich.
All data members are private.

Furthermore this class is able to compare sandwiches based on the Comparable interface with the Generic Sandwich.

NOTE: You WILL NOT write any additional methods.
Sandwich(String, int, String[]) - Constructor for class cscd211Classes.Sandwich
Represents the constructor to build a Sandwich object.
SandwichCaloriesComparator - Class in cscd211Comparators
This class imposes a total ordering based on the calories of each Sandwich
The class implements a Comparator that ensures that two Sandwich objects are passed in.
SandwichCaloriesComparator() - Constructor for class cscd211Comparators.SandwichCaloriesComparator
You DON"T NEED to write this constructor.
selectionSort(Comparable[]) - Static method in class cscd211Utils.ArrayUtils
The selectionSort must be written by you, meaning you can't call any builtin Java sorts.
setUp() - Method in class cscd211Lab1.CSCD211W17Lab1Tests
